                    <h2><a href="/en/blog/22545-Slax-7.0.9-beta-release.html" style="color: #333333;">Slax 7.0.9 beta release</a></h2>
                    <p align=justify>Hello everybody. After few months of silence, the Beta release of Slax 7.0.9 is now available for testing. It features Linux Kernel 3.9.7, KDE 4.10.4 and FireFox 22.0. It is a bit bigger than usual, since FireFox started to require icu4c for some strange reason, which is 7MB packed (!) ... I have to find out if this dependency can be dropped.</p><p>
In the mean time, please feel free to test this beta release and let me know if you recognize anything unusual. Your feedback will help make Slax better. Thank you very much for using Slax! :)</p><p>
Download Slax 7.0.9-beta:<br>
<a href="http://www.slax.org/download/7.0.9beta/slax-7.0.9-beta-i486.iso">32bit ISO</a><br>
<a href="http://www.slax.org/download/7.0.9beta/slax-7.0.9-beta-i486.zip">32bit ZIP</a><br>
<a href="http://www.slax.org/download/7.0.9beta/slax-7.0.9-beta-x86_64.iso">64bit ISO</a><br>
<a href="http://www.slax.org/download/7.0.9beta/slax-7.0.9-beta-x86_64.zip">64bit ZIP</a><div class="bottom50"><i class="icon-user"></i> <a href="/en/blog/22545-Slax-7.0.9-beta-release.html#comments">61 comments</a>&nbsp; <i class="icon-eye-open"></i> <a href="/en/blog/22545-Slax-7.0.9-beta-release.html#firstnew">61 new</a></div>
